    <p>I have this plant (right). Is it a pep­per­mint or spearmint? Vivi­enne Lee</p>
    <p>The mint is nei­ther a spearmint nor a pep­per­mint. It is likely a cul­ti­var of the Ja­panese men­thol mint (Men­tha ar­ven­sis var piperas­cens), which is char­ac­terised by a high men­thol con­tent in its leaves.</p>
    <p>It is known lo­cally as “icy mint” due to the sen­sory re­sponse to­wards the men­thol found in the leaves.</p>
    <p>Have a gar­den­ing query? E-mail it with clear, high­res­o­lu­tion pic­tures of at least 1MB, if any, and your full name to stlife@ sph.com.sg. We re­serve the right to edit and re­ject ques­tions.</p>

